OpenCodeProxyHub is an independent project licensed under the MIT License.

This project is derived from and substantially inspired by:

  opencode-free-proxy
  https://github.com/bigdata2211it-web/opencode-free-proxy

The original project declares the MIT License in its package metadata and README.

OpenCodeProxyHub reimplements and extends the original project's core
compatibility behavior, including:

- exposing OpenCode free models through OpenAI-compatible and Anthropic-compatible endpoints
- forwarding requests to the OpenCode Zen API
- using the required x-opencode-* upstream request headers
- model compatibility behavior for free model IDs
- OpenAI/Anthropic message conversion concepts
- API-key based local access control concepts

OpenCodeProxyHub has since been substantially rewritten and expanded with:

- TypeScript and Fastify backend architecture
- React/Vite Web UI
- hashed and recoverable API key management
- model and settings persistence
- proxy pool and chained proxy support
- rate limiting
- observability
- Docker Compose deployment

OpenCodeProxyHub is not affiliated with OpenCode, opencode-free-proxy, or any
upstream service provider.

